1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,952
ServerScout AI Risk Briefing Assistant is an AI-assisted security reporting workflow.

2
00:00:06,232 --> 00:00:10,240
It helps small teams understand scan results quickly.

3
00:00:10,520 --> 00:00:15,368
This demo uses the verified local build and the packaged prototype.

4
00:00:15,648 --> 00:00:19,416
Small teams often receive technical scan data.

5
00:00:19,696 --> 00:00:23,872
They still need a clear answer about what should be fixed first.

6
00:00:24,152 --> 00:00:28,640
They also need to explain why the risk matters to stakeholders.

7
00:00:28,920 --> 00:00:43,344
ServerScout includes dashboard, asset management, scan tasks, vulnerability management, topology, attack surface visualization, external intelligence, report export, and the new AI Briefing page.

8
00:00:43,624 --> 00:00:49,864
The integrated AI Briefing page takes scan evidence and generates a readable risk brief.

9
00:00:50,144 --> 00:00:52,808
Click Generate AI Brief.

10
00:00:53,088 --> 00:00:56,448
The output provides an executive summary.

11
00:00:56,728 --> 00:01:01,576
It also provides remediation priorities and report-ready language.

12
00:01:01,856 --> 00:01:05,144
The AI layer does not replace scanning.

13
00:01:05,424 --> 00:01:09,600
It helps users translate scan data into decisions.

14
00:01:09,880 --> 00:01:16,144
Those decisions include what is urgent, why it matters, and what should be written in the report.

15
00:01:16,424 --> 00:01:25,040
This is useful for small businesses, internal IT teams, freelance security testers, and junior security engineers.

16
00:01:25,320 --> 00:01:34,200
The business model starts with free local use, then grows into team subscriptions, per-report pricing, and consultant packages.

17
00:01:34,480 --> 00:01:44,656
Next steps are connecting the assistant to live scan task data, adding a secure model gateway, and generating PDF report sections from scan evidence.

18
00:01:44,936 --> 00:01:51,824
For HackOnVibe, this AI assistant helps small teams move from scan output to remediation action.

